snippet.title: The Room Where She Died by ALISSA
snippet.description:
Thanks for watching! Can't wait to share more with you! ⚓️

The Room Where She Died

I stand, lost in shadows of,
Years of lament etched into four walls.
Like a whisper, 
A feverish dream.

Where only echoes respond,
I keep asking - how long?

This caravan follows a hearse,
Leaving the Room where she died.
Dying begins at birth.
To suffer is the way of our kind.

Let lies sit like baskets of,
Flowers in bloom,
Colours bright and false.
She will dance on Hyperion’s field.

Where I’m still wondering why,
She hit her head on the sky?

To be alive is only to acknowledge time as it is.
Do you remember the feeling of being alive with lightning in your mind?
Sinners and saints join the broken and brave in this memory plane.
We’re all the same.

Cold are your nights.
Hours will pass as you strangle time.
Dead are your eyes.
Nevertheless all the corpses still waltz by your side.

Pain walks on broken feet.
A broken heart keeps the beat.
Still she hums softly.

Looking through cloudy window panes,
Without moving for ever and a day.
Then the light comes to greet her face, 
And brush the dust from her broken brain.

Eyes say what the voice cannot.
Is this where it ends?
Here, our paths must part.
Just a helpless spectator, am I.

And I keep questioning “god”,
To drown out the ferryman’s calls.

Vocals performed, recorded and written by Alissa White-Gluz
Music by Oliver Palotai
Drums by Alex Landenburg
Video script by Alissa White-Gluz
Video by iCode

snippet.title: IT: Welcome to Derry (2025) | Episode 6 Trailer | HBO Max
snippet.description:
#ITWelcomeToDerry 

🎥 Attention viewers! (ITS FAN MADE)
Dive back into the terrifying world of Stephen King with this Welcome to Derry concept, featuring a Final Trailer along with Episode 6 and Episode 7 promo-style moments. Inspired by the chilling universe of IT, this edit captures the horror, mystery, and rising darkness surrounding Pennywise as the town of Derry unravels. Featuring characters like Jovan Adepo and Taylour Paige and the vision of Andy & Barbara Muschietti, this fan-made trailer reflects the tone of HBO’s original series style—packed with tension, atmosphere, and cinematic horror. Watch this HBO Max-inspired concept trailer as the nightmare continues to grow beneath the streets of Derry.

The inspiration behind this video:
Experience the chilling atmosphere of Welcome to Derry as the story intensifies in the IT Welcome to Derry Final Trailer. With new footage revealed in the IT Welcome to Derry Episode 6 Promo and the highly anticipated IT Welcome to Derry Episode 7 Promo, HBO continues expanding Stephen King’s terrifying universe. This latest look from HBO Max, HBO, and HBO Originals showcases the darkness returning to the iconic town of Derry, bringing viewers deeper into the origins of Pennywise.

Crafted by Andy Muschietti and Barbara Muschietti, the series dives into the haunting mythology behind IT Movies, blending cinematic horror with the depth of an HBO Original Series. With stars like Jovan Adepo, Taylour Paige, and the legacy of Bill Skarsgård, the Derry trailer delivers suspense, psychological terror, and a chilling look at the creature that has traumatized generations. Fans following HBO Max Trailer, HBO Max Teaser, HBO Max Series, HBO Max Originals, and HBO Max YouTube updates are calling this one of the most intense horror expansions yet.

As excitement grows across the community, major trailer channels such as FilmSpot Trailer, MovieGasm, KinoCheck, EmergencyAwesome, and IGN TV Trailer continue covering every detail and breakdown. Whether you're searching for HBO Trailer, New on HBO, or the next chapter in this IT TV Show, this new promo delivers everything horror fans want. Prepare to return to Derry—where every shadow whispers, and Pennywise is never truly gone.

snippet.description:
#themandalorian #leakedtrailer #starwarscelebration  

Watch the 'FAN (CONCEPT) Trailer Concept' For Star Wars The Mandalorian And Grogu (2026)  (More Info About This Video Down Below!)

▶️ Watch More Concept Trailers:

SOLO 2: A Star Wars Story Trailer - https://youtu.be/vCmBvA1j68I 👈

AHSOKA Season 2 Trailer -  https://youtu.be/jQ289yp9c6o 👈

Crimson Dawn : A Star Wars Story Trailer -  https://youtu.be/GtKwWMqrjV8 👈

"The Mandalorian & Grogu (2026)" marks the Mandalorian saga’s thrilling return to the big screen under the visionary direction of Jon Favreau, with a screenplay co-written by Favreau and Dave Filoni. This highly anticipated film transports fan-favorite duo Din Djarin and Grogu from their Disney+ appearances into a cinematic scale adventure. Pedro Pascal reprises his role as the stoic Din Djarin, while Grogu continues to captivate audiences through a blend of animatronics, puppetry, and advanced visual effects.

Joining Pascal and Grogu is an esteemed ensemble cast: Sigourney Weaver stars as a commanding New Republic colonel named Ward, who oversees critical missions following the fall of the Empire. Jeremy Allen White voices the now-grown Rotta the Hutt—once Jabba’s son—taking him in a new, muscular gladiator direction. Jonny Coyne returns as the imposing Imperial warlord leading remnants of the Empire, while characters like Garazeb “Zeb” Orrelios and members of the Anzellan species make appearances, deepening the narrative continuity with the Disney+ series.

Scheduled for release on May 22, 2026, "The Mandalorian & Grogu" serves as the first theatrical installment in the Star Wars franchise since The Rise of Skywalker (2019). Although a trailer has not yet been released to the public, exclusive footage debuted at D23 2024 and Star Wars Celebration 2025, offering glimpses of Grogu training, AT-ATs in snowy terrain, and exciting action sequences. Directed and produced by Favreau, with Kathleen Kennedy and Dave Filoni also at the helm, the film promises to deliver a standalone cinematic experience that both longtime fans and newcomers can enjoy.

◁ On our channel, we create trailer mashups ▷ Trailer mashups, also known as recut trailers, are crafted by gathering various film footage from one or more movies and re-editing them to form a brand-new trailer. These mashups often depict a movie that doesn’t exist or shift the genre of an existing film. As derivative works defined under the United States Copyright Act 17 U.S.C. § 101, they may be protected from copyright claims under the fair use doctrine.

Trailer mashups are not just a form of user-generated digital creativity but also a unique way to build excitement for upcoming releases, complementing official movie trailers. While traditional trailers tease the plot and generate hype, fan-made mashups let the audience put their own cinematic twist on existing footage. This creative freedom can spotlight a particular actor, emphasize a specific storyline, or even transform the film’s genre entirely.

This video is a parody. Due to its derivative and transformative nature, it is protected under Fair Use.

"The Mandalorian & Grogu (2026)" marks the Mandalorian saga’s thrilling return to the big screen under the visionary direction of Jon Favreau, with a screenplay co-written by Favreau and Dave Filoni. This highly anticipated film transports fan-favorite duo Din Djarin and Grogu from their Disney+ appearances into a cinematic scale adventure. Pedro Pascal reprises his role as the stoic Din Djarin, while Grogu continues to captivate audiences through a blend of animatronics, puppetry, and advanced visual effects.

Joining Pascal and Grogu is an esteemed ensemble cast: Sigourney Weaver stars as a commanding New Republic colonel named Ward, who oversees critical missions following the fall of the Empire. Jeremy Allen White voices the now-grown Rotta the Hutt—once Jabba’s son—taking him in a new, muscular gladiator direction. Jonny Coyne returns as the imposing Imperial warlord leading remnants of the Empire, while characters like Garazeb “Zeb” Orrelios and members of the Anzellan species make appearances, deepening the narrative continuity with the Disney+ series.

Scheduled for release on May 22, 2026, "The Mandalorian & Grogu" serves as the first theatrical installment in the Star Wars franchise since The Rise of Skywalker (2019). Although a trailer has not yet been released to the public, exclusive footage debuted at D23 2024 and Star Wars Celebration 2025, offering glimpses of Grogu training, AT-ATs in snowy terrain, and exciting action sequences. Directed and produced by Favreau, with Kathleen Kennedy and Dave Filoni also at the helm, the film promises to deliver a standalone cinematic experience that both longtime fans and newcomers can enjoy.

snippet.description:
Simply Red - Holding Back The Years (Live from Santiago)

Simply Red are thrilled to announce 'Recollections', their brand-new album celebrating 40 incredible years! Featuring 40 newly recorded versions of their most loved songs, the album will be available digitally, on 4LP vinyl, as a 3CD set, and as a 2LP highlights edition, out November 21. Pre-order it here: https://SimplyRed.lnk.to/RecollectionsYT

Tickets for the Simply Red 40th Anniversary Tour are available now! Get yours at https://www.simplyred.com

Subscribe to Simply Red - https://www.youtube.com/@simplyred/featured?sub_confirmation=1

Follow Simply Red:

https://twitter.com/SimplyRedHQ
https://instagram.com/simplyredofficial
https://www.tiktok.com/@simplyredofficial
https://www.threads.net/@simplyredofficial

Simply Red have over a billion hits on YouTube, have sold over 60 million albums worldwide, 5 going to number one in the UK. Their 1991 classic Stars was the best-selling album for two years running in Britain and Europe. They have had two US Billboard chart toppers with classic singles Holding Back The Years and If You Don’t Know Me By Now. Every Simply Red studio album has been a UK top ten (with previous release Big Love reaching number 4 in 2015). Hucknall has been the songwriter and bandleader since the beginning in 1985.

Holding back the years
Thinking of the fear I've had so long
When somebody hears
Listen to the fear that's gone
Strangled by the wishes of pater
Hoping for the arms of mater
Get to me the sooner or later

I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on

Holding back the years
Chance for me to escape from all I've known
Holding back the tears
Cause nothing here has grown
I've wasted all my tears
Wasted all those years
And nothing had the chance to be good
Nothing ever could yeah, oh

I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
So tight

I've wasted all my tears
Wasted all of those years
And nothing had the chance to be good
Cause nothing ever could, oh, yeah
Oh...

I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
Holding, holding, holding

That's all I have today
It's all I have to say

#SimplyRed #Recollections #HoldingBackTheYears
